## Transformation matrix

Define $\bT_2: \mathbb{R}^R \to \mathbb{R}^S$ such that $\bpi \mapsto \bpi_2$.
To illustrate, consider $p=3$ so that $R=2^3=8$ and $S=3+3=6$.

$$
\myoverbrace{
\left(
\begin{array}{c}
\dot\pi_1 \\
\dot\pi_2 \\
\dot\pi_3 \\
